title: How to find the symbol table in a TI DSP. (TMS320C5510)
content: That's it, just want to know how to find the symbol table in a binary I pulled from a DSP chip. I know it could be stripped, just don't know how to tell.

comments.text: I don't know about that specific DSP, but it's fairly common to compress binaries with a loader stub in devices - did you try to run binwalk over it?
Did you check the manufacturer's documentation ?! ( ti.com/lit/ug/spru423i/spru423i.pdf )
